===Etymology 2===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|わた|alt=棉:rare,草綿:rare}}
{{swp|ja:}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=わた|-}}, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|sort=わた|*wata}}. Cognate with {{cog|ryu|綿|tr=wata}}.

Originally referred to any [[batting]] or [[stuffing]], which was generally unspun [[silk]]. The meaning shifted after the spread of [[cotton]] in the {{w|Muromachi period}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|わた|acc=2|acc_ref=DJR}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|わた}}

# the [[cotton]] plant
# raw [[cotton]]
# [[batting]] or [[stuffing]]
# the [[albedo]] of a [[citrus]]; or the [[pith]]/[[placenta]] of a [[pepper]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|アルベド|tr1=arubedo|t1=[[albedo]]}}
# {{lb|ja|sort=わた|metaphor}} the state of being [[exhausted]] or extremely [[tired]] {{qualifier|likely from the hard work required to pick cotton}}
#: {{ja-usex|'''綿'''のように疲れた|'''わた''' の よう に つかれた|to be as tired as '''cotton''' → to be [[exhausted]]}}

